<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h1>My First JavaScript</h1>
<p>Here, a JavaScript changes the value of the src (source) attribute of an image.</p>

<script>
function light(sw) {
  var pic;
  if (sw == 0) {
    pic = "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
  } else {
    pic = "pic_bulbon.gif"
  }
  document.getElementById('myImage').src = pic;
}
</script>

<img id="myImage" src="https://www.google.com/url?sa=i&url=https%3A%2F%2Ftheaveragescientist.co.uk%2F2022%2F06%2F28%2Fwhy-does-it-get-dark-at-night%2F&psig=AOvVaw3PMp37WIwmulrudbIS4VtQ&ust=1729795431890000&source=images&cd=vfe&opi=89978449&ved=0CBQQjRxqFwoTCMCOjKeUpYkDFQAAAAAdAAAAABAE" width="100" height="180">

<p>
<button type="button" onclick="light(1)">Light On</button>
<button type="button" onclick="light(0)">Light Off</button>
</p>

</body>
</html>

